Former Arsenal star Cesc Fabregas caught up with Gunners legend Bob Wilson on Wednesday as the duo took part in 'Stars On Canvas' for UK charity Willow.

Having previously spent eight years in north London, the Spanish midfielder controversially joined rivals Chelsea from Barcelona in the summer.

However, having changed his allegiance from the red of Arsenal to the blue of Chelsea, Fabregas was all smiles with his old pal Wilson from his time at Highbury and the Emirates.

